==Japanese==
=== Etymology ===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[土]] || [[曜]] || [[日]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
From Latin ''[[dies Saturni]]'' ("day of Saturn") through Indian astrology in the fifth century as Sanskrit ''[[zanivāra]]'' (''zani'', "of the planet Saturn") into Buddhist astrology in the eighth century as 土曜日: [[土]] (ど, ''do'', "earth", the Buddhist element associated with the planet Saturn) + [[曜日]] (ようび, ''yōbi'', "day of the week").

===Noun===
{{janoun|どようび|doyōbi}}
# [[Saturday]]

====Synonyms====
* [[土曜]]

